techmeme.title: The US Copyright Office says using AI tools to assist in creative processes doesn't compromise copyright protections as long as the content has human authorship (Gene Maddaus/Variety)
Vandatrack: retail traders bought a net $562M of Nvidia's stock on January 27, a record, and $360M on January 28, after DeepSeek's AI model sent NVDA crashing (Financial Times)
Huawei adds DeepSeek's R1 to its ModelArts Studio platform, saying the free model is "Ascend-adapted", referencing its data center GPUs, but offers few details (Matthew Connatser/Tom's Hardware)
Ampere: users spent $465M on Microsoft games in December, making it the biggest publisher, ahead of EA's $366M; Call of Duty HQ had 38M MAUs in November 2024 (Christopher Dring/Video Games Chronicle)
Comcast starts rolling out its "pioneering new, ultra-low lag connectivity experience" to select US cities, using the L4S standard to significantly cut latency (Jay Peters/The Verge)
